reviews.review_text: This establishment is unpretentious and needs no recomendations, but do not be disuaded by the store front s modesty. If you enjoy Malaysian food, specifically soup or stew with curry and coconut milk, then you will enjoy the flavours served here. Apart from base ingredients being ready, each bowl will be made to order. If you like it hot (spicy) they will be happy to comply and the same can be said for a milder palete. We ordered two; one bowl of chicken curry with noodles and another bowl of Laksa. The Chicken Curry was enriched with coconut milk and a red-curry broth with just the right amount of heat. I asked for hot   and it had a perfect kick to enjoy every drop! Every once in a while, a bite into a potato that had been stewing in the broth was a delight. The chicken was tender and sooooo full of flavour that I wanted more, but honestly I did not feel there wasn t enough, I just didn t want it to end, in fact the only time I felt sad was when I saw the bottom of the bowl. The Laksa with noodles, tasted like it was made with coconut and a spicy fish broth (slightly milder than the coconut curry). With large chunks of fried tofu, fish cake, shrimp, chicken and hard boiled egg, there was no shortage of mouth-party suprizes! Is it worth coming here? Why ask me? Just stand and watch the steady line of happy loyal customers who by their presence alone will testify to great food, good value and quick effecient service.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for leaving us a review. We look forward to serving you again soon!

reviews.review_text: If I could offer you only one tip for the future, it would be always tip at Hawkers Delight. Long-term benefits of tipping at Hawkers Delight have been proved by scientists. Whereas the rest of my advice has no basis more reliable than my own meandering experience. I will dispense this advice now.

Get the laksa! Its one of the best Ive ever tasted and a big portion. Inflation has caught up to this restaurant, which used to be known for dirt cheap delicious food, but the prices are still pretty cheap. Be aware this place is the definition of hole-in-the-wall so its all counter service and inside of the restaurant can feel pretty cramped.

reviews.review_text: I ordered delivery at this place from Uber Eats. The dishes I ordered were Fried Kuey Teow and Vegetable Fritters. Food is affordable and tastes amazing! They dont cheap out on ingredients! Best of all, they gave me a receipt of the food! So if I enjoy the food, next time I can order the same dish! A lot of take outs Ive ordered dont provide that. They just write the persons name on the dish. A big difference in experience~ Fried Kuey Teow: I taste more sea food and veggies than noodles! They dont cheap out on ingredients! On top of that, they put the right amount of flavour in my opinion. Amazing would definitely order again! Vegetable Fritters: Crispy on the outside and soft on the inside. For $1.85 they provide 2. The 2 vegetable fritters are big so definitely worth the price! Even tho it was weird they provided the food in a paper bag, I didnt mind it. Paper means eco friendly! Overall, a bang for your buck! I have never tried these foods before so this was a delight!

reviews.review_text: One of my favorite spots in the city. The food might be be $4.75 any more but the value for money for a dinner here is still amazing. Food here is as good as more expensive spots downtown. Their kway teow is my top pick. I have never recommended to someone and had them not love it. Veggie options are also diverse and delicious. Food can be a bit greasy, but at this place you won t mind it. Hawkers might look a little run down but it is always clean, the food comes quick, and the service is great.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for leaving us a review. We look forward to serving you again soon!

reviews.review_text: This place kept us alive in university. Excellent meat and veg options. Order at the counter and take a number style service, but so cheap and so good. We just went again after years away and its exactly as greasy and delicious. The prices have only gone up about $2 since the old days. Incredible value.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for leaving us a review. We look forward to serving you again soon!

reviews.review_text: Came in for a quick lunch spot. The mee goreng is delicious and would highly recommend. No frills experience but the food was worth it!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for leaving us a review. We look forward to serving you again soon!

reviews.review_text: This place is tiny, cramped, loud and the food is REALLY GOOD!!  If youre looking for a comfortable place to eat this is probably not the place for you - there are only  a few tables and chairs and some bar stool counter seats near the front window and side wall and this place is usually  full of people.   However, whatever wait or line up is worthwhile once you have tried the food.  The veggie fritters are addicitive.  Their char kuey teow and  goreng dishes are delicious as is the laksa and gado gado.  Large portions, cheap and served up quickly.  Cash only.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for leaving us a review. We look forward to serving you again soon!

reviews.review_text: Prices are great. Food is great. Beware that this is a cash only place. Theres a decent selection of dishes which cost under 10 dollars here but everything is under 15 or 16 dollars. Im a big fan of their veggie fritters. Good texture in a syrup sauce
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for leaving us a review. We look forward to serving you again soon!

reviews.review_text: Absolutely top-notch, old-school Asian take-out place. Not fancy, cash only, no smoke will be blown in your ear. A throwback to the days before 25th and Main became whatever it is now. Ive never been to Singapore but friends who have tell me the taste is authentic.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for leaving us a review. We look forward to serving you again soon!

reviews.review_text: This family has been serving me amazing food since they opened.  Whenever I leave town for work they are first on my mind when I return.  Mee Pok is my go to, but the Haianese chicken rice, the Laksa, the curries - so good.  Cheap, tasty eats.  Hard working family.  A Vancouver treasure.  Support them.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for leaving us a review. We look forward to serving you again soon!

reviews.review_text: Amazing food.  Got the vegetable curry and Nas Goreng.  $30 all in with 2 drinks.  Enough food to feed 4 and tasty too.

reviews.review_text: Its busy. You get no service. It seems kinda dingy. But the food is awesome. Yeah there isnt any service and they can be snappy, but who cares? They arent rude and its one of the best fast food restaurants in Main. Try the Chae Kway Teow with pickled jalapenos!

reviews.review_text: Small eatery with great food. The prices were reasonable and portion size was great. Must visit for flavorful food.

reviews.review_text: Delightful Asian/Singaporean street food favourites in a crowded space. I like the laksa and nasi goreng. I also recommend getting the vegetable fritters; theyre cheap and quite tasty for an appetizer. You line up, order at the counter, take a number and try to find a seat. They seem to do a lot of takeout business as well.

reviews.review_text: Delicious food reminds me of being back in Singapore. The place has been around for ages. Dont expect any frills when ot comes to service or decor with this hole in the wall. The food is good. Cash only! No debit or credit. Vancity bank/ATM is half a block away.

reviews.review_text: After returning from 15 years in Asia we ve finally found an authentic Singapore Malay restaurant for our favourites. Roti prata, laksa, char kway teow, chicken rice and more. Even the impolite service is authentic.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for leaving us a review. We look forward to serving you again soon!

reviews.review_text: Singaporean/ Malaysian cuisine like a hawker stall - One of my favourites for over a decade.  This place breaks the rule of cheap, fast and good- you can only pick two.  Unbelievably priced, fast service and the food is generous and delicious.  The seating area and ambiance is like a cafe, so I recommend doing take-away / take-out. Lamb curry, nasi goreng, hainan chicken, mee goreng, and some roti to go please! No need to advertise - they are busy busy busy. Try it.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much for leaving us a review. We look forward to serving you again soon!
